      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented SQA plan with version control and regression testing in place for all FEA solvers used in the ensemble.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA platforms (FDA in-house code, Ansys 2022 R2, DePuy Synthes internal solver) operate under ISO 9001-compliant SQA plans. Version control logs and regression test suites were reviewed and found current."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions solved to within solver-specified tolerance; results documented.",
      "rationale": "Each solver was exercised against NAFEMS benchmark LE1 (plane stress elliptic membrane) and a cantilever beam with end load. All solvers reproduced reference solutions within 0.5%, satisfying the Gradation 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic mesh refinement study demonstrating QoI convergence; GCI or equivalent error estimate reported and below 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted on the pedicle screw shank and rod-screw interface. Richardson extrapolation-based GCI for peak von Mises stress was 2.1%; stiffness QoI GCI was 0.8%. Final mesh (1.2 M elements, hex-dominant) adopted for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error below 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear quasi-static analyses used Newton-Raphson iteration with force residual tolerance 1e-7. Energy balance error across all 11 model instances remained below 0.05%. No convergence failures observed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup by a second analyst; checklist-based verification of boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions.",
      "rationale": "A second FEA analyst independently reviewed all model input decks against a 47-item checklist covering geometry, mesh, material cards, contact pairs, and load/BC definitions. Two minor annotation discrepancies were identified and corrected prior to production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented justification for constitutive model selection (elastic-plastic with isotropic hardening); comparison to alternative model forms reported.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V screw and CoCr rod modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening calibrated from tensile coupon data. A purely linear-elastic alternative was evaluated and found to over-predict stiffness by 14% beyond yield, confirming the necessity of the plastic model. UHMWPE vertebral body surrogates modeled as linear elastic per ASTM F1717 protocol."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and geometric inputs sourced from traceable measurements or certified material data sheets; input uncertainty characterised via Monte Carlo sampling with documented distributions.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (E, yield stress, tangent modulus) sourced from lot-specific tensile testing (n=5 coupons per lot). Geometric dimensions (screw OD, thread pitch, rod diameter) measured with CMM on production hardware. Input uncertainty was characterised by fitting normal distributions to measured variability and propagating through the FEA ensemble using 1000-sample Monte Carlo; output distribution statistics are reported in the validation evidence package. This comprehensive Monte Carlo UQ across all inputs provides full probabilistic coverage of the input space."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 specimens from production lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to nominal geometry within drawing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (n=6 Lab A, n=5 Lab B). All specimens drawn from a single production lot; CMM inspection confirmed all critical dimensions within ±0.05 mm of nominal. Lot traceability documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading configurations; at minimum two load configurations or loading rates evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed exclusively under the ASTM F1717 standard compression-bending configuration at quasi-static rate. Only a single test condition was evaluated; no variation in loading angle, offset distance, or rate was explored. This represents a known gap relative to the required level; accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard configuration and the COU is limited to that protocol."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs directly correspond to measured experimental specimen properties; any discrepancies quantified and shown to be within measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "FEA material inputs were set to the lot-specific measured mean values for each specimen batch. Geometric inputs were set to CMM-measured nominal dimensions. Residual discrepancies between model inputs and experimental specimen properties were quantified as less than 1.5% for all parameters, within combined measurement uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval computed for each QoI; E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 9 for stiffness (1.31), yield force (1.74), and force at 40 mm (0.98). All values below the 1.96 threshold. Validation uncertainty uval includes experimental measurement uncertainty, numerical solution uncertainty, and input parameter uncertainty propagated from the Monte Carlo UQ activity."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements; justification documented.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs mandated by ASTM F1717 and cited in FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. These QoIs directly characterise the two primary failure modes (fatigue initiation and gross deformation) relevant to clinical use."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario geometry, loading, and boundary conditions match the COU; any differences between validation and COU conditions assessed and shown to be non-material.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity replicates the COU exactly: same implant design, same ASTM F1717 protocol, same UHMWPE vertebral body surrogates, same quasi-static loading rate. No extrapolation beyond the validated configuration is claimed. The COU is explicitly bounded to the ASTM F1717 static compression-bending regime."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; this shortfall is accepted because the COU is explicitly limited to the ASTM F1717 standard configuration and no extrapolation to other loading conditions is claimed. Quantitative validation metrics (E/uval) satisfy acceptance criteria for all three primary QoIs. Uncertainty quantification via comprehensive Monte Carlo sampling was completed across all model inputs and results are incorporated into the E/uval calculation. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level decision for regulatory submission.",
